.TH "HPC\-COMPOSE\-SWEEP\-OBSERVE" "1" "" "hpc\-compose 0.1.49" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hpc\-compose\-sweep\-observe \- Parse and rank trial objectives for one sweep
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
hpc\-compose sweep observe [OPTIONS]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
Read each terminal trial's objective (from a log regex or JSON artifact), write it back to the sweep manifest, and print a ranked table. With \-\-watch \-\-stop\-when, poll until the objective condition is met and then stop the sweep.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB-f\fR, \fB--file\fR \fIFILE\fR
Compose specification file to read; if omitted, use the active context compose file or fall back to compose.yaml.
.TP
\fB--sweep\-id\fR \fIID\fR
Sweep id to observe; defaults to the latest sweep.
.TP
\fB--watch\fR
Poll until a terminal trial satisfies \-\-stop\-when, then stop the sweep.
.TP
\fB--stop\-when\fR \fIEXPR\fR
Stop condition, e.g. `objective < 0.05` or `objective > 0.9` (matches the sweep.objective.direction).
.TP
\fB--poll\-interval\fR \fIDURATION\fR
Polling interval for \-\-watch. Default: 30s.
.TP
\fB--timeout\fR \fIDURATION\fR
Give up watching after this duration; 0s watches without a deadline.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fIFORMAT\fR
Output format. Possible values: text, json.
.TP
\fB--scaling\fR
Print a post\-hoc scaling report (objective vs sweep.objective.scaling_axis: log\-log slope + efficiency table) over terminal trials.
.TP
\fB--squeue\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the squeue executable. Default: squeue.
.TP
\fB--sacct\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the sacct executable. Default: sacct.
.TP
\fB--scancel\-bin\fR \fIPATH\fR
Path to the scancel executable (used by \-\-watch \-\-stop\-when). Default: scancel.
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
